        Parse Record IO data

        Main function which parses and converts IO data from given byte array.

        Parameters:
        bytes - requires for reading data
        bytesToTake - parameter used for selecting required byte length (1,2,4,8)
        extended - parameter used for parsing special data such as codec 8 extended.
        Returns:
        returns record IO element object.

      • setTakeByte

        public void setTakeByte(int takeByte)

        Take byte

        Sets variable takeByte to 2 or 4, depends which codec is used. codec 8 uses 2 bytes, while extended codec 8 uses 4 bytes.

        Parameters:
        takeByte - takes int for selecting bytes.
